en_239257_0	Responding positively to a request of the Provincial Blood Centre at Kilinochchi District Hospital, the General Officer Commanding, 57 Division, Major General Vijitha Ravipriya, made arrangements for conduct of a blood donation programme at Kilinochchi Hospital premises on Sunday (16) with close coordination with members of the medical staff.
en_239257_1	Dr H. M. D. R. B Hindagoda and a medical team at the District Hospital assisted the project with the support of the nurses.
en_239257_2	30 Army personnel including Officers, belonging to Brigades and Battalions under the 57 Division donated their blood for use of patients in Kilinochchi during the campaign.
en_239257_3	Some volunteers in the area too gave their blood during the event.
